fields.title: Masala Dosa
fields.description: Crisp rice crepe filled with spicy potato mash.
fields.process:
Soak rice and urad dal, grind to batter, and ferment overnight.
Boil potatoes, mash them with sautΘed onions, green chillies, and spices.
Spread batter on a hot tawa, drizzle oil, and cook dosa till crisp.
Place masala filling inside and fold the dosa.
Serve hot with coconut chutney and sambar.

fields.title: Aloo Paratha
fields.description: Stuffed flatbread with spiced potato filling, served with curd.
fields.process:
Knead wheat flour dough with salt and water, rest for 30 mins.
Mash boiled potatoes with green chillies, coriander, and spices.
Roll dough, fill with potato mix, and seal edges.
Roll again and roast on tawa with ghee or oil till golden spots.
Serve with curd and pickle.

fields.title: Chocolate Cake
fields.description: A moist, fluffy and rich chocolate cake with a decadent chocolate buttercream frosting.
fields.process:
Mix flour, cocoa powder, baking powder, and sugar in a bowl.
Whisk eggs, milk, oil, and vanilla essence together.
Combine wet and dry ingredients, fold in well.
Pour into a greased tin and bake at 180░C for 30û35 mins.
Cool, frost with chocolate ganache or icing, and serve.

fields.title: Poha
fields.description: Light, fluffy flattened rice tossed with onions and peanuts.
fields.process:
Rinse poha, drain, and keep aside.
Heat oil, add mustard, curry leaves, green chillies, and onions.
Add peanuts, turmeric, salt, and sautΘ well.
Mix in poha, toss gently, and cook for 2 minutes.
Garnish with coriander and lemon juice, serve hot.

fields.title: Upma
fields.description: Savory semolina porridge cooked with veggies and spices.
fields.process:
Dry roast rava (semolina) till aromatic, set aside.
Heat oil, add mustard, urad dal, curry leaves, green chillies, and onions.
Pour water, salt, and bring to a boil.
Add rava gradually, stirring to avoid lumps.
Cook till water is absorbed, garnish with coriander.

fields.title: Pesarattu
fields.description: Green gram pancake served with ginger chutney.
fields.process:
Soak green gram (moong dal) overnight, grind with ginger, green chillies, and salt.
Heat a tawa, pour batter, and spread like dosa.
Sprinkle chopped onions and cumin seeds on top.
Drizzle oil, cook both sides till crisp.
Serve hot with ginger chutney.

fields.title: Egg Bhurji
fields.description: Indian-style scrambled eggs with onions and spices.
fields.process:
Heat oil, sautΘ onions, green chillies, and tomatoes.
Add spices like turmeric, chilli powder, and salt.
Break eggs directly into the pan, scramble well.
Cook till eggs turn soft and fluffy.
Garnish with coriander and serve with roti or pav.

fields.title: Chole Kulche
fields.description: Spicy chickpeas paired with soft flatbreads.
fields.process:
Soak and pressure cook chickpeas with salt and tea bag till soft.
SautΘ onions, ginger-garlic paste, tomatoes, and spices in oil.
Add cooked chole and simmer with garam masala and coriander.
Serve with soft, buttered kulchas.
Garnish with onions, lemon wedges, and coriander.

fields.title: Pongal
fields.description: Creamy rice-lentil dish tempered with ghee and pepper.
fields.process:
Dry roast moong dal lightly and wash with rice.
Pressure cook rice and dal with salt and lots of water till soft.
Temper cumin, pepper, ginger, curry leaves, and cashews in ghee.
Add to cooked rice-dal mixture and mix well.
Serve hot with coconut chutney or sambar.

fields.title: Dhokla
fields.description: Soft, fluffy steamed gram flour cake with mustard tempering.
fields.process:
Mix besan (gram flour), curd, water, turmeric, and salt to a batter.
Add eno or baking soda before steaming for fluffiness.
Pour into greased plate and steam for 15û20 mins.
Temper mustard seeds, green chillies, curry leaves in oil.
Pour tempering over dhokla, cut into pieces, and serve.

fields.title: Chocolate Silk
fields.description: A delicious silk choclate that contains badam and khaju for extra taste.
fields.process:
Melt dark chocolate and fresh cream together over a double boiler.
Whisk till smooth, silky, and glossy.
Chill the mixture for a few hours to thicken.
Pipe or spoon into glasses and top with chocolate shavings.
Serve chilled as a rich dessert.

fields.title: Butter Chicken
fields.description: Tender chicken cooked in creamy, spiced tomato gravy.
fields.process:
Marinate chicken with curd, spices, and grill or fry till half done.
SautΘ butter, ginger-garlic paste, and tomato puree till cooked.
Add spices, kasuri methi, cream, and cooked chicken.
Simmer on low till chicken is tender and gravy thickens.
Garnish with cream and coriander, serve with naan or rice.

fields.title: Paneer Butter Masala
fields.description: Cottage cheese in a rich, buttery tomato sauce.
fields.process:
SautΘ butter, onions, ginger-garlic paste, and tomatoes till soft.
Blend to a smooth paste and cook with spices and cream.
Add paneer cubes and simmer for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle kasuri methi and garam masala.
Serve hot with roti, naan, or jeera rice.

fields.title: Hyderabadi Biryani
fields.description: Aromatic basmati rice cooked with marinated meat.
fields.process:
Marinate chicken/mutton with curd, spices, and fried onions for 2 hours.
Parboil basmati rice with whole spices.
Layer meat and rice in a biryani pot with mint, coriander, and saffron milk.
Seal and dum-cook on low flame for 40û45 minutes.
Serve with mirchi ka salan and raita.

fields.title: Fish Curry
fields.description: Tangy, spicy fish curry with tamarind base.
fields.process:
Marinate fish with turmeric, salt, and chilli powder.
SautΘ onions, ginger-garlic paste, and tomatoes till soft.
Add spices, water, tamarind pulp, and simmer.
Gently drop fish pieces and cook on low flame till done.
Garnish with coriander and serve with rice.

fields.title: Palak Paneer
fields.description: Cottage cheese cooked in smooth spinach gravy.
fields.process:
Blanch spinach leaves, grind to a smooth paste.
SautΘ onions, ginger-garlic paste, and tomatoes with spices.
Add spinach puree, cream, and simmer.
Add paneer cubes, cook for 5 minutes on low flame.
Serve with roti, naan, or rice.

fields.title: Gongura Chicken
fields.description: Spicy chicken cooked with tangy sorrel leaves.
fields.process:
Cook cleaned gongura (sorrel leaves) till soft, mash and keep aside.
SautΘ onions, green chillies, ginger-garlic paste, and spices.
Add chicken pieces and cook till tender.
Mix in cooked gongura paste and simmer till masalas coat chicken.
Serve hot with rice or jowar roti.

fields.title: Veg Pulao
fields.description: Fragrant rice cooked with mixed vegetables and spices.
fields.process:
Heat ghee/oil, fry whole spices and sliced onions.
Add mixed vegetables and sautΘ for 2 minutes.
Stir in soaked basmati rice and water, adjust salt.
Cook covered on low flame till rice is fluffy.
Garnish with coriander and serve with raita.

fields.title: Chicken Chettinad
fields.description: Fiery chicken curry with freshly ground masala.
fields.process:
Dry roast coconut, fennel, pepper, cumin, cinnamon, and cloves, grind to a paste.
SautΘ onions, ginger-garlic paste, and tomatoes till soft.
Add chicken pieces, turmeric, and chilli powder, cook till sealed.
Stir in ground masala paste, water, and simmer till chicken is tender.
Garnish with coriander and serve hot with rice or dosa.

fields.title: Bagara Baingan
fields.description: Egg plants simmered in peanut-coconut sesame gravy.
fields.process:
Dry roast peanuts, sesame, coconut, and grind with spices to a paste.
Slit brinjals and shallow fry them till half-cooked.
SautΘ onions, ginger-garlic paste, and the masala paste.
Add tamarind pulp, water, and fried brinjals, simmer till soft.
Garnish with coriander and serve with biryani or rice.

fields.title: Chapati with Dal Tadka
fields.description: Wheat flatbread served with tempered lentils.
fields.process:
Knead wheat flour with water and salt into a soft dough.
Roll and roast chapatis on a hot tawa with light ghee.
Cook toor/moong dal with turmeric, salt, and mash well.
Temper mustard, cumin, garlic, red chillies, and curry leaves in ghee.
Pour over dal, garnish with coriander, and serve with hot chapatis.

fields.title: Kadai Paneer
fields.description: Kadai paneer is a restaurant style delicious spicy paneer recipe made with fresh ground kadai masala, paneer, onions, tomatoes & bell peppers.
fields.process:
Dry roast coriander seeds and red chillies, grind to a coarse powder.
SautΘ onions, ginger-garlic paste, and capsicum in oil.
Add tomatoes, salt, turmeric, and the ground kadai masala, cook till oil separates.
Toss in paneer cubes, kasuri methi, and simmer for 5 minutes.
Garnish with coriander and serve hot with naan or roti.

fields.title: PineAplle Cake
fields.description: This cake is full of crushed pineapple for flavor and moisture.
fields.process:
Beat butter and sugar till creamy, then add eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour, baking powder, and fold into the batter with pineapple pieces.
Pour into a greased tin and bake at 180░C for 30û35 minutes.
Cool the cake, optionally frost with whipped cream and pineapple slices.
Chill before serving for best taste.

fields.title: Semiya Upma
fields.description: Vermicelli also called bambino is an easy and quick recipe with lots of vegetables which makes for a good breakfast.
fields.process:
oast vermicelli (semiya) lightly until golden and set aside.
Heat oil, mustard seeds, curry leaves, chopped green chilies, and onions till fragrant.
Add chopped vegetables (optional) and sautΘ briefly.
Pour water, salt, and bring to a boil.
Add roasted vermicelli, cook till water is absorbed, garnish with coriander, and serve hot.

fields.title: Tamarind Sambar
fields.description: Sambar is a South Indian lentil stew made with pigeon pea lentils, tamarind and a unique spice blend called sambar powder.
fields.process:
Boil toor dal with turmeric and mash it well.
Soak tamarind, extract pulp, and keep aside.
Cook chopped vegetables with salt and sambar powder.
Add tamarind pulp, mashed dal, and boil till flavors blend.
Temper with mustard, curry leaves, red chillies, and serve hot.

fields.title: Mutton Biryani
fields.description: Mutton Biryani is a guaranteed crowd-pleaser! This flavorful dish is a hit at my house.
fields.process:
Marinate mutton with curd, spices, ginger-garlic paste, and rest 2 hours.
Cook basmati rice with whole spices till 70% done.
SautΘ onions, green chillies, tomatoes, and marinated mutton in a biryani pot.
Layer rice and mutton with fried onions, mint, and coriander.
Dum cook on low flame for 40û45 minutes and serve with raita.

fields.title: Egg Biryani
fields.description: Egg Biryani is a must-try recipe for all egg lovers as it promises to take your love for eggs to another level altogether.
fields.process:
Boil eggs, peel, and shallow fry with salt and spices.
Cook basmati rice with whole garam masala till 90% done.
In a pan, sautΘ onions, green chillies, tomatoes, and biryani masala.
Layer rice and masala alternately with fried eggs, mint, and fried onions.
Dum-cook for 15û20 minutes, serve hot with raita.

fields.title: Paneer biryani
fields.description: Paneer Biryani is a super satisfying vegetarian meal with aromatic, fluffy basmati rice and pillowy soft chunks
fields.process:
Marinate paneer cubes with curd, biryani masala, and lemon juice.
Cook basmati rice with spices till 80% done.
SautΘ onions, ginger-garlic paste, tomatoes, and spices in ghee.
Layer masala, paneer, and rice with mint, coriander, and fried onions.
Dum-cook on low for 20 minutes, serve with raita or salan.

fields.title: Chicken Hyderabadi Dum Biryani
fields.description: Chicken Biryani is a fragrant and flavorful rice dish packed with tender chicken pieces marinated in yogurt and a blend of spices.
fields.process:
Marinate chicken with curd, spices, fried onions, lemon juice, and mint for 2û3 hours.
Parboil basmati rice with whole spices.
In a biryani pot, layer marinated chicken and rice alternately, adding saffron milk and fried onions.
Seal with dough and dum-cook on low flame for 45û50 minutes.
Serve hot with mirchi ka salan, raita, and lemon wedges.

fields.title: Apricot Delight
fields.description: Apricots are a staple of summer. And theyÆre delicious in their purest form, which is fresh, sweet, and juicy.
fields.process:
Soak dried apricots in warm water till soft, then mash coarsely.
Cook apricot pulp with sugar till it thickens slightly.
Layer crushed biscuits at the base of a glass dish.
Pour apricot mix, top with whipped cream and chopped nuts.
Chill for a few hours and serve cold as a dessert.

fields.title: Chicken Samosa
fields.description: An unbelievably delicious and easy chicken samosa recipe with a crispy, golden crust and the tastiest spiced chicken filling.
fields.process:
Cook minced chicken with onions, ginger-garlic paste, green chillies, and spices.
Let the filling cool completely.
Prepare samosa dough with maida, salt, oil, and water.
Roll, cut, fill with chicken mixture, shape into cones, and seal.
Deep fry till golden brown and crispy, serve hot with chutney.

fields.title: Dhahi Puri
fields.description: Dahi Puri is popular chaat snack that is crispy on the outside and soft on the inside.
fields.process:
firstly, make a hole at the centre of puri with your thumb.
further, stuff half tsp of boiled potatoes into each puris.
furthermore, take a cup of curd and mix sugar in it.
further add green chutney onto each puri.
then also top with a tsp of curd.
sprinkle chili powder, chaat masala and black salt or cooking salt.
finally, garnish with coriander leaves and serve sev puri immediately.

fields.title: Egg Bhajji
fields.description: This is a mouth-watering snack recipe which is prepared by boiling eggs and then dipping into a batter made of flour and spices.
fields.process:
Hard boil eggs, peel them, and cut them in half.
Mix all the ingredients for batter to a smooth paste.
Heat oil for deep frying.
Dip the halved eggs in the batter and fry in hot oil till golden.
Drain on to some paper towel.
Serve with ketchup

fields.title: Khasta Kachori
fields.description: Kastha Kachori is a delicious, spicy, fried puffed pastry and filled with spicy moong dal mixture and then deep fried.
fields.process:
Take the dough and knead it for a minutes. Divide the dough in twelve equal parts.
Take one part of the dough and with your fingers flatten the edges and make into 3-inch circle.
Fry them on medium-low heat. After they start to puff, slowly turn them over. Fry until golden-brown on both sides. If the kachoris are fried on high heat, they will get soft and will not be crispy.
Kachories can be stored for at least a week in an airtight container

fields.title: Gunta Ponganalu
fields.description: Gunta Ponganalu or Kuzhi Paniyaram is a savory dish made with left over dosa batter.
fields.process:
Prepare dosa or idli batter and mix in chopped onions, green chillies, coriander, and cumin.
Heat a ponganalu (appe) pan and add a little oil in each cavity.
Pour batter into the cavities and cook on medium flame.
Flip when the sides are golden and cook the other side.
Serve hot with coconut chutney or peanut chutney.

fields.title: Chicken 65 Biryani
fields.description: Chicken 65 biryani combines the flavors of Chicken 65, a spicy, deep-fried chicken dish, with aromatic biryani rice.
fields.process:
Marinate chicken with curd, spices, ginger-garlic paste, and fry till crispy.
Cook basmati rice with whole spices till 90% done and set aside.
In a pan, sautΘ onions, green chillies, tomatoes, and biryani masala.
Layer fried chicken and rice alternately, adding fried onions, mint, and coriander.
Dum cook for 20 minutes on low flame and serve hot with raita.

fields.title: Fish Biryani
fields.description: Lightly spiced fish biryani made with a yogurt biryani sauce and cooked in one pot with layered fish, rice and saffron.
fields.process:
Marinate fish pieces with spices, lemon juice, and shallow fry till golden.
Cook basmati rice with whole garam masala till 90% done.
In a pot, fry onions, green chillies, tomatoes, and biryani masala.
Layer fish and rice alternately with mint, coriander, and fried onions.
Dum cook on low flame for 15û20 minutes and serve with lemon wedges.

fields.title: Gutti Vankaya Curry
fields.description: Gutti Vankaya, a South Indian delicacy, beckons you into a world of rich spices and culinary charm.
fields.process:
Prepare stuffing with roasted peanuts, sesame, coconut, and spices.
Slit small brinjals and stuff them with the masala paste.
Fry the stuffed brinjals in oil till partially cooked.
Add tamarind pulp, water, and remaining masala, simmer till brinjals soften.
Garnish with coriander and serve with hot rice or roti.

fields.title: Kaddu Ki Kheer
fields.description: Kaddu ki kheer with jaggery is an easy-to-cook, delectable dessert, made using red pumpkin, milk, ghee,  jaggery, saffron, cashews, and raisins.
fields.process:
Peel and grate bottle gourd (kaddu), squeeze out excess water.
Boil milk and simmer till it slightly thickens.
Add grated bottle gourd and cook till soft and milk reduces.
Stir in sugar, cardamom powder, and cook for 5 more minutes.
Garnish with fried cashews, raisins, and serve warm or chilled.

fields.title: Chicken Tikka
fields.description: Chicken tikka is a popular chicken dish in South Asia and amongst the South Asian diaspora.
fields.process:
Marinate boneless chicken pieces with curd, ginger-garlic paste, lemon juice, and tikka spices.
Rest the marinated chicken for at least 2 hours.
Skewer the pieces with capsicum, onion, and tomato slices.
Grill on charcoal or tawa, basting with butter till cooked and charred.
Serve hot with green chutney, onion rings, and lemon wedges.

fields.title: Mexican Street Corn (Elote)
fields.description: This side is perfect for any cookout staple—try it with BBQ chicken or grilled steak—or, at a party, you could set up all of the toppings (adding a few wildcards, like scallions, crumbled bacon, and sriracha) and create a Build Your Own Elote Bar.
fields.process:
Prepare a grill for medium-high heat; heat 5 minutes (or preheat a grill pan over medium-high heat).

Grill corn, turning often, until slightly charred all over, about 10 minutes. 
Meanwhile, in a small bowl, mix mayonnaise and crema.

Transfer corn to a platter. Brush with mayonnaise mixture. Top with cotija, chili powder, and cilantro. Serve warm or at room temperature with lime wedges alongside.

fields.title: Puppy Chow Recipe
fields.description: Puppy chow is a classic Midwestern snack and one of our all-time favorite no-bake desserts. It’s made from Chex cereal, melted chocolate, peanut butter, butter and any other toppings you’d like to add.
fields.process: Prepare our basic puppy chow recipe using Reese’s spread instead of peanut butter. When shaking the cereal mixture with powdered sugar in a large plastic bag, add halved mini peanut butter cups and Reese’s Pieces candy. Shake and pour onto a flat surface to set.

fields.title: Savory Cracker Snack Mix
fields.description: a friend suggested I make it even more versatile with something other than oyster crackers. Now it’s a deliciously addictive snack!
fields.process: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, combine potato sticks, crackers and pretzels. In a small saucepan, melt butter; stir in remaining ingredients. Drizzle over cracker mixture; toss to coat.

fields.title: Club Roll-Ups
fields.description: Packed with meat, cheese and olives, these roll-ups are always a hit at parties.
fields.process: In a small bowl, beat the cream cheese, ranch dressing and salad dressing mix until well blended. In another bowl, combine the bacon, onion, olives, pimientos and jalapenos.

fields.title: Savory Cracker Snack Mix
fields.description: After trying a snack mix with the flavors of my favorite Everything bagel seasoning, a friend suggested I make it even more versatile with something other than oyster crackers.
fields.process: 3/4 cup: 306 calories, 20g fat (7g saturated fat), 20mg cholesterol, 468mg sodium, 26g carbohydrate (1g sugars, 1g fiber), 5g protein.

fields.title: Chocolate Mocha Dusted Almonds
fields.description: I love to make recipes with nuts. These are chocolaty with a hint of coffee—elegant and addictive! I give them away as gifts.
fields.process:
Microwave chocolate chips, covered, at 50% power, stirring once or twice, until melted, 3-4 minutes. Stir until smooth. Add almonds; mix until coated.
Refrigerate until chocolate is set. Store in an airtight container in refrigerator.

fields.title: Quick Tortilla Pinwheels
fields.description: Fun to make and easy to enjoy, easy tortilla pinwheels are a food everyone will love and that you can customize in many ways.
fields.process: Combine the first 6 ingredients in a bowl; spread mixture on 1 side of each tortilla and roll up tightly. Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour. Slice into 1-in. pieces. Serve with salsa or picante sauce.

fields.title: Antipasto Skewers
fields.description: Antipasto skewers—the finger-friendly Italian kabobs with marinated vegetables, cheeses and tortellini— are precisely what you need for your next gathering.
fields.process: Use bite-sized cheese tortellini to ensure they stay securely on the skewers and are easy to eat. You can use refrigerated, frozen or dried tortellini; just cook them according to the package instructions before marinating them.
